

PETALING JAYA:
 AirAsia X Bhd (AAX) has announced additional flight frequencies to eight destinations in its route network, including Melbourne, Sydney, Perth, Osaka, Sapporo, Beijing, Shanghai and Taipei.

In a statement yesterday, AAX said it is also offering promotional all-in fares for economy seats from as low as RM259 one-way to Perth; RM329 one-way to Hangzhou; RM429 one-way to Busan; RM459 one-way to New Delhi; RM509 one-way to Sapporo. 

The low-cost airline said guests can make bookings from now until May 8, 2016 to travel immediately until Nov 24, 2016 on these low fares.






















